HEADWORD: Jasperize
<hw>Jas"per*ize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Usually p. p.
<er>Jasperized</er> (<?/).]</ety> <def>To convert into, or make to
resemble, jasper.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Polished specimens of <qex>jasperized</qex> and agatized
woods.</q> <rj><qau>Pop. Sci. Monthly.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

